cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.MM

This paper deals with image processing and computer vision techniques to erase text from natural scene images. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes an inpainting CNN model for text erasing, which involves deep learning techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely category. The paper also discusses the training process and the evaluation of the proposed method, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible category. The paper also mentions the use of a novel scene text detection method, which involves information retrieval techniques, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) another possible category. Finally, the paper deals with natural scene images, which are often used in multimedia applications, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible category.
